&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 6 Midwife&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a dedicated Passionate, Highly Motivated, Very well organised , forward thinking Midwife who has a passion for providing exceptional women centered care enjoys working as part of a multidisciplinary team .&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt; This Midwife would join our busy FMU / CFC Units at Imperial College Healthcare NHS Trust.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; This role involves working across site between St Mary&#39;s /Queen Charlottes &lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; As well as FMU /CFC there is an element Continuity of Care for Twins / Multiples Involved.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; We want a Midwife who would contribute to a safe, effective and quality driven Fetal Medicine Service &lt;br /&gt; This role involves care and support to women diagnosed with Fetal Abnormalities such as Structural or Genetic,.&lt;br /&gt; Supporting women with either Twins/ Multiples throughout their pregnancy &lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Our aim is to ensure safe running of Imperial FMU /CFC &lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; The successful Candidate need to be comfortable in working in this dynamic and demanding area.&lt;br /&gt; This role is full time 37 ½ hours per week&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For additional information please do contact:&lt;/p&gt;
